<TITLE> Budget to have PPP funds </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)The upcoming will have block allocation for the public-private partnership alongside development and revenue expenditure, the finance minister said on Tuesday. "Development initiatives will be taken in education, health and infrastructure sectors through the PPP and of course, the power will get the priority," AMA Muhith told reporters. "There will be three budgets in the 2009-10 fiscal yearthe PPP will be added alongside revenue and development budgets," the minister said after meeting a delegation of the Bangladesh Association of Banks, an organisation of private bank entrepreneurs. The move aims to foster concerted efforts of the public and private sectors and allow the private sector greater role in development. "We're hopeful of a positive outcome," the minister said. Muhith said the GDP will grow at six percent in the current 2008-09 fiscal year despite the ongoing global economic recession. But the year was going to be tough because of the financial downturn. The BAB delegation led by chairman Nazrul Islam Majumder asked the minister to cut the interest rate of saving bonds. The minister told reporters that there will be no rate cut now. bdn
